## TypeScript Standards (Required)

### Strict Mode

**TypeScript strict mode is enabled**

```json
// tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true
  }
}
```

### Type Annotations

**Explixt types required**

**Rules:**

- All function parameters must have types
- All function return types must be explicit
- Public properties must have types
- No `any` type (use `unknown` if truly dynamic)

```typescript
// ✅ DO: explicit types everywhere
export class UserService {
  private apiUrl: string = '/api/users';

  getUser(id: number): Observable<User> {
    return this.http.get<User>(`${this.apiUrl}/${id}`);
  }

  parsePayload(data: unknown): User {
    if (!isUser(data)) throw new Error('Invalid payload');
    return data;
  }
}

// ❌ DON'T: implicit or any types
getUser(id) { ... }           // missing parameter type
getUser(id: number) { ... }   // missing return type
parse(data: any) { ... }      // any type
```

### Immutability

**Prefer readonly and const**

```typescript
// ✅ DO: readonly for properties that should not be reassigned
export class AppConfig {
  readonly apiBase: string = 'https://api.example.com';
  readonly maxRetries: number = 3;
}

// ✅ DO: readonly arrays and objects
export class NavComponent {
  readonly navItems: readonly NavItem[] = [
    { label: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { label: 'About', path: '/about' },
  ];
}

// ❌ DON'T: mutable properties that are never reassigned
export class AppConfig {
  apiBase: string = 'https://api.example.com';
}
```

### Interface vs Type

**Use interfaces for object shapes**, types for unions/intersections

```typescript
// ✅ DO: interface for object shapes
export interface User {
  readonly id: number;
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

// ✅ DO: type alias for unions and intersections
export type Status = 'active' | 'inactive' | 'pending';
export type AdminUser = User & { role: 'admin' };

// ❌ DON'T: type alias for plain object shapes
export type User = {
  id: number;
  name: string;
};
```

