## Accessibility (Required)

### Sematic HTML

**Use semantic elements** instead of generic divs

```html
<!-- ✅ DO: semantic HTML elements -->
<header>
  <nav aria-label="Main navigation">
    <ul>
      <li><a routerLink="/">Home</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>
</header>

<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Page Title</h1>
    <section aria-labelledby="section-heading">
      <h2 id="section-heading">Section</h2>
      <p>Content</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>

<footer>
  <p>&copy; 2026 Asian American Church</p>
</footer>

<!-- ❌ DON'T: div soup -->
<div class="header">
  <div class="nav">
    <div class="nav-item"><a routerLink="/">Home</a></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

